cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for compressing sentence embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image-based sentence embeddings, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for evaluating the effectiveness of the proposed methods, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques for learning compressed sentence representations, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
